  "prompt": "What constitutes as a good small group question/topic?",
  "response": "A good small group discussion question or topic should have several key characteristics:\n\n1. Open-ended\n- Encourages multiple perspectives\n- Cannot be answered with a simple \"yes\" or \"no\"\n- Allows for deeper exploration\n\n2. Thought-provoking\n- Challenges participants to think critically\n- Sparks genuine curiosity\n- Invites personal reflection\n\n3. Relevant\n- Connects to the group's purpose or context\n- Relates to participants' experiences\n- Timely and meaningful\n\n4. Specific yet flexible\n- Clear enough to provide direction\n- Broad enough to allow diverse responses\n- Offers multiple angles of discussion\n\n5. Promotes engagement\n- Encourages everyone to participate\n- Not intimidating or too personal\n- Allows quieter members to contribute\n\nExamples across different contexts:\n\nSpiritual/Church Group:\n- \"How have you experienced God's guidance during challenging times?\"\n- \"What does authentic community mean to you?\"\n\nProfessional Development:\n- \"What leadership qualities have most influenced your career?\"\n- \"How do you balance innovation with established practices?\"\n\nPersonal Growth:\n- \"What personal values guide your major life decisions?\"\n- \"How do you define success beyond professional achievements?\"\n\nThe best questions invite vulnerability, reflection, and meaningful dialogue.",
